> > I'm pretty familiar with braizing because of bicycle frames- can anyone
> > comment on or say why braising wouldn't work on small panel holes as it
> > uses a much lower temp than welding?
> 
> Brazing a panel hole shut? I'd be worried about trapping flux in an
> inaccessible part of the panel (flux is corrosive if you don't get it off).
> If you can get all of the flux off the panel, brazing should work well.

or use a non corrosive flux.

